chad bonaker arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe visiting artists chad bonaker at stanford 2011 2012 hosted at stanford by drama department bonaker a stage lighting and digital design artist is a visiting instructor in technical theater with the drama department about chad bonaker chad bonaker has been designing lighting for the theater since 1995 when he was offered the opportunity to design gaieties in his sophomore year at stanford university that experience so sparked his interest in lighting that the following year he took a class in lighting from peter maradudin who was filling in for michael ramsaur while the latter was on sabbatical when michael returned he took mr bonaker on as protege a relationship that continues to this day lighting has enabled mr bonaker to travel the world he has designed shows in shang hai china belgrade serbia and all over the western united states in 2005 he received his mfa from the college conservatory of music at the university of cincinnati he currently is the resident designer at the utah festival opera in logan utah and at children's musical theater in san jose california he has designed for several bay area theater companies including broadway by the bay theatreworks mountain view stanford summer theater and west bay opera chad bonaker's website home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
